Interface TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MethodRegistry.Default.Compiled.Entry, TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.Simple, TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.Skip
    Enclosing interface:
    TypeWriter.MethodPool

    public static interface TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry
    An entry of a method pool that describes how a method is implemented.
    See Also:
    TypeWriter.MethodPool

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.Factory
      A factory for creating a TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.
      static class  TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.Simple
      A default implementation of TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry that is not to be ignored but is represented by a tuple of a byte code appender and a method attribute appender.
      static class  TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry.Skip
      A skip entry that instructs to ignore a method.

        The byte code appender to be used for the instrumentation by this entry. Must not be called if isDefineMethod() returns false.
